1. Types of leave - guidelines and overview

 

1.1. Earned Leave

  • Where applicable, Earned Leave days are vacation days provided for taking planned and paid time off from normal work routine. This time away from work helps you manage how, when and for what purpose the time off is taken based on your work/life needs and priorities. For details, please refer to your respective state's table below in Section 2 of this Policy.
  • This leave is accrued on a pro-rated basis, fortnightly. This is applicable to new joiners as well.
  • You must seek approvals in advance (through email or any other communication means) from your People Lead prior to proceeding on leave to facilitate smooth work operations.
  • You must charge your Earned Leave to "Earned Leave" in the Time and Expense reporting application.
  • In case of cessation of employment during the fiscal year: Your Earned Leave encashment will be subject to respective state specific requirements. If you have utilised your Earned Leave entitlement for the entire fiscal year in advance, the excess leave will be adjusted against any amounts, including salary and full and final amounts, payable to you.

Note: Earned Leave can also mean Privileged leave (as prescribed in your respective state).

 

1.2. Sick & Wellness Leave

  • You are entitled to certain Sick & Wellness Leave, as per state specific requirements. For details, please refer to your respective state's table below in Section 2 of this Policy.
  • For availing Sick & Wellness Leave, you must inform (through email or any other communication means) your People Lead as soon as possible on the first day of absence itself or as soon as reasonably practical. However, in case of unforeseen circumstances (accidents etc.) you or your immediate family member/s may inform the People Lead as early as possible, for Accenture to be able to facilitate applicable assistance per our policies or procedures.
  • You must charge your Sick & Wellness Leave to "Sick & Wellness Leave" in the Time and Expense reporting application.
  • Subject to such state requirements or limits (as applicable), if you need Sick & Wellness Leave for five (5) consecutive working days or more, then a medical certificate/ equivalent medical advice or prescription from your doctor is required and your People Lead will approve the leave only after the aforesaid documents are provided.
  • For current employees, the entire entitlement of Sick & Wellness Leave is provided upfront in the beginning of the fiscal year. For new joiners this leave is pro-rated based on the day of joining in the fiscal year. The total pro-rated balance will be available to a new hire at the time of joining.

 

Note: While you are provided with the entitlement in totality, in the event you have utilized this leave in excess of your pro-rated value (during exit), the same will be recovered from/adjusted against any amounts, including salary and full and final amounts, payable to you.

1.3. Casual Leave

  • Where applicable, Casual Leave is provided to enable you to take care of your personal matter/s. For details, please refer to your respective state's table below in Section 2 of this Policy.
  • Casual Leave can be taken for up to two consecutive days at a time within a fortnight. You must inform your People Lead (through email or any other communication means) as soon as reasonably practical.
  • For Casual Leave more than two consecutive days, you must seek approval from your People Lead (through email or any other communication means) prior to availing leave.
  • You must charge your Casual Leave to "Casual Leave" in the Time and Expense reporting application.
  • For current employees, the entire entitlement of Casual Leave is provided in totality during the beginning of the fiscal year. For new joiners this leave is pro-rated based on the day of joining in the fiscal year. The total pro-rated balance will be available to a new hire at the time of joining.

Note: While you are provided with the entitlement in totality, in the event you have utilized this leave in excess of your pro-rated value (during exit), the same will be recovered from/adjusted against any amounts, including salary and full and final amounts, payable to you.

1.4. Other Definitions

 

Accenture Leave Year/Fiscal Year

Our leave year is consistent with our fiscal year i.e., September 1 to August 31.

Carry forward of leave

The leave balance that you can carry forward at the end of fiscal year based on the defined limit as per state wise leave entitlement.

Leave Encashment

Encashment of leave is subject to criteria as prescribed in your respective states. Any payment to you for leave encashment is subject to prevailing tax laws.

State

For the purpose of this policy, "State" shall mean the Indian state in which your Accenture's base office location (as tagged in Workday) is situated. 

Working day

Will be considered based on working hours as applicable to you. Please refer to India supplement to Policy 0063_C19 – Time and Expense Reporting.

 

Note:

  • Any unauthorized leave will be treated as a misconduct or unapproved absence and may lead to disciplinary action/s. For more details, please refer to India Policy 0864 – Misconduct.
  • Excess leave, unless approved in accordance with this policy, will be considered as unapproved absence and liable to necessary deductions/appropriate actions/loss of pay.

3. Applicability during Permanent Location transfer

 

In the event of your relocation, as per India supplement to Policy 0044_C19 – Permanent Location Transfer, if your new base location is in a different state, then your leave entitlements and accruals will be pro-rated.

 

Note: 

  • Transfers while serving notice period post resignation are not permissible.
  • At all times, your Accenture base location will be considered for encashment calculation.

4. Applicability when on Global Careers Program (GCP)

 

If you are proceeding on temporary international transfer assignment/transfer as per India Policy 750_C19 – International Temporary Transfers for Groups, the below shall apply to you:

  • Any unutilized Earned Leave in India is frozen for the period of the transfer (up to a maximum of the carry forward limit as per state-wise entitlement, applicable to your Accenture base location) and you can use this balance only upon repatriation and resumption of employment in India.
  • The treatment of any unutilized Sick & Wellness Leave and/or Casual Leave will be in accordance as per state-wise requirement.
  • In the event of your separation from Accenture (from host location), the encashment of your unutilized frozen Earned Leave balance will be in accordance as per state-wise requirement.
  • Upon return, if you move to a different state, the principle as mentioned in the Transfer section of this policy will apply.  
  • If you are on temporary international transfer assignment/transfer etc., inclusive of successive assignment without a gap, the total fixed pay for leave encashment calculation will be your last drawn total fixed pay in India.

5. Leave for part-time work arrangement

 

The state-wise entitlement remains unaffected, however the working hours for calculation/proration/accrual or any other administrative purposes will align to the part time working hours as applicable to you. 

 

6. Leave with Loss of Pay and Unpaid Leave of Absence (Unpaid LoA)

  • For leave requests beyond leave entitlements, if you have exhausted your current Earned Leave (EL) balance (i.e., inclusive of EL carry forward balance from previous year and the EL entitlement for the current fiscal year) - you may avail up to 5 consecutive working days of "Leave with Loss of Pay" in a fortnight, subject to approvals. You will need to charge this on Time and Expense reporting application directly under "Leave with Loss of Pay". 
  • For leave requests beyond 5 working days, upon exhaustion of your available Earned Leave (EL) balance (inclusive of EL carry forward balance from previous year and the EL entitlement for the current fiscal year) - you are required to raise a request on Accenture Service Tool for Unpaid Leave of Absence (Unpaid LoA). Please refer to Policy 0595 – Other Approved Absence for more information.

7. Exceptions

 

All exceptions are at the sole discretion of Accenture and will be based on specific nature of circumstance at hand. The same requires an approval of the respective Group Lead or Function Lead or an Accenture Leader and the Group HR Lead who is an Accenture Leader.
